metatags.twitter:title: I am STILL in a realm of shock and sheer joy. | Jayla Simone Meeks
metatags.og:title: I am STILL in a realm of shock and sheer joy. | Jayla Simone Meeks
metatags.og:description:
I am STILL in a realm of shock and sheer joy. Female Founders Pitch Night with the  Build in Tulsa Team was an experience like no other. Winning $11,000 to get MedGlow (the first medical aesthetics booking app for women of color) off the ground. For years I have worked with women across the nation, as we work to build confidence through prioritizing health and fitness, without surgery. I am so grateful for this funding, as it will allow me to leverage the expertise of my amazing team to create equity in the non-surgical segment of the beauty industry. 

Being a Young, Black, and Female Founder is tough. 

Right now, Black women entrepreneurs receive less than 1% of Venture Capital. Female Founders Pitch Night created the space I needed to build my confidence because my ideas were seen and heard. This experience connected me with other Female Founders that are facing the difficulties that I am, and instead of positioning us against one another we truly pushed one another to be better.
